# Root-level env is unused by CRWLA — each app reads its own .env:
#   apps/api/.env       (see apps/api/.env.example)
#   apps/web/.env.local (see apps/web/.env.local.example)
#   apps/mobile         (uses app.json `expo.extra` or EXPO_PUBLIC_* vars)
#
# This file is kept only as a marker so accidental `cp .env.example .env`
# at the repo root doesn't fail.
